elements.title: Naples International Airport
elements.description: The start of the journey. Giorno Giovanna arrives here and defeats Luca 'Leaky-Eye' after a dispute over taxi scams. This is where his path first crosses with Passione. (March 29, 2001, Morning)

elements.title: Naples Funicular
elements.description: Giorno meets Bruno Bucciarati here while investigating Luca's death. Their initial confrontation and battle takes place on the funicular. (March 29, 2001, Afternoon)

elements.title: Marina Grande, Capri
elements.description: After joining Team Bucciarati, their first mission is to retrieve Polpo's hidden treasure. They take a boat from Naples to the island of Capri, arriving at Marina Grande, and face Mario Zucchero. (March 30, 2001)

elements.title: Ruins of Pompeii
elements.description: The gang is tasked with protecting Trish Una. Here, they are ambushed by Illuso and his Stand, 'Man in the Mirror,' within the ancient ruins. (March 30, 2001, Afternoon)

elements.title: Venezia Santa Lucia Station
elements.description: The team travels towards Venice via express train to find a key. The train becomes a battlefield against Prosciutto's 'The Grateful Dead' and Pesci's 'Beach Boy'. They arrive at this station after the intense fight. (March 31, 2001)

elements.title: Ponte della Libert, Venice
elements.description: While driving into Venice over this long causeway bridge, Giorno and Mista are attacked by Ghiaccio and his incredibly powerful freezing Stand, 'White Album'. (March 31, 2001, Afternoon)

elements.title: San Giorgio Maggiore, Venice
elements.description: The team retrieves the final clue from the top of the bell tower on this island. Their escape by boat is interrupted by the terrifying flesh-eating Stand, 'Notorious B.I.G.'. (April 1, 2001)

elements.title: Costa Smeralda, Sardinia
elements.description: To uncover the Boss's identity, the team (now traitors to Passione) travels to Sardinia. Near this location, Narancia faces Squalo and Tiziano, and later, the terrifying battle between Doppio/Diavolo and Risotto Nero takes place. (April 2-3, 2001)

elements.title: The Colosseum, Rome
elements.description: The final destination. The gang meets Jean-Pierre Polnareff, who has the Stand Arrow. The climactic battle against Diavolo and his 'King Crimson' takes place in and around this ancient amphitheater. (April 5, 2001)

elements.title: Tiber River, Rome
elements.description: During the final battle, the Stand Arrow falls into the Tiber. Giorno pierces Gold Experience with it, unlocking its ultimate form: Gold Experience Requiem, which ultimately defeats Diavolo. (April 5, 2001, Late Afternoon)

elements.title: Golden Wind Journey
elements.description: The approximate route taken by Team Bucciarati across Italy, from Naples to their final confrontation in Rome.

messages.content: Show me all the key places Giorno and the gang visited in Jojo's Bizzare Adventure Part 5: Golden Wind. Give approximate dates and times for each location visited. Be very specific about the locations! If they were real places, I want to go visited them. Plot their route also

I have marked all the key locations from *Golden Wind* on the map and drawn the route of the gang's journey across Italy.

From their beginnings in Naples, to the mission in Capri, the ambush in Pompeii, the deadly train ride to Venice, the flight to Sardinia, and the final, world-altering battle in Rome, you can now see their entire path.

Click on any pin to read about the dramatic events that unfolded at that location. You can also use the timeline slider at the bottom to follow their progress chronologically. I hope this helps you visualize their bizarre and heroic adventure
